HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1281
By Bulso
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Houston Fulks on
being named the 2025 WILLCO Awards Boys'
Bowler of the Year.
WHEREAS, we are pleased to recognize and commend those successful high school
athletes who, through their magnificent exploits, bring honor to Tennessee and serve as
exceptional ambassadors of this State; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable individual is Houston Fulks of Franklin High School, an
athlete of extraordinary talent, skill, and dedication, who has proven himself to be a formidable
competitor in bowling; and
WHEREAS, in recognition of his success on the lanes, Houston Fulks has been named
the WILLCO Awards Boys' Bowler of the Year for the second consecutive year; and
WHEREAS, Houston Fulks epitomizes all that is good in today's student athlete, as he
has achieved a high level of success as a bowler while evincing great character; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Fulks's notable achievements are a source of great pride for his family,
his community, and his school, and it is appropriate that we recognize this accomplished
athlete; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Houston Fulks on being named the 2025
WILLCO Awards Boys' Bowler of the Year, wishing him much success and happiness in his
future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
